Barnes, Respondent, v. Keene, Appellant. (Superior Court of New York City, General Term. June 27, 1890.) Appeal from jury term. Action by Lucien Barnes against James R. Keene.

*958Argued before Freedman and Truax, JJ.

Shipman, Barlow, Larocque & Choate, for appellant. S. H. Randall, for respondent. Per Curiam.

Upon the whole case no error appears which constitutes ground for reversal; nor can it be held that the verdict is excessive. The •judgment and order should be affirmed, with costs.
